				<b><a href="javascript:openWindow(10,496969);"><font face="Verdana" size="1" >10</font></a></b>
				<font face="Verdana" size="1"><b>best</b></font>
			</td>
		</td>
		
	
	</tr>
	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I agree with most of RPGers comments, except, I believe that /ooc should be in place...there will be times when a zonewide broadcast may be necessary/relevant, whatever.  In text-based rp, people use /ooc to do their out-of-character chatting, so I think /ooc should be retained for the same purpose. albeit perhaps with some modifications.  However, I do agree that /shout should be eliminated. Also, what to do with /auction ?<BR>
As for the /say command, I don't agree that it should be expanded.  If it is, what does it do, but replace /shout and create the same anti-roleplaying aspect?<BR>
<BR>
Again, the name verification is a must, I think.  I wonder why there are name restrictions for the other servers at ALL, since I see violation after violation AFTER freakin' violation all the time.  On an RP server, name-verification is an absolute necessity.  I am unable to take seriously a character who's name is mycbbeltmule.  <BR>
<BR>
And might I add, since there are those of us who would like very much to rp loner characters, some consideration might be given to those who would prefer to solo.  I understand that EQ is a multi-player game, but the fact remains that there are a large number of players who would PREFER to SOLO.  In an rp setting, where the name of the game is not pwrlvling for as much experience in as little time as possible, but actual, sure-'nuff roleplay, it would be nice for a player to be able to traverse the land and its inhabitants without being forced to do so with a group, merely to survive.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
